Burial of Galileo | Wellcome Collection|https://wellcomecollection.org/works/v88mzjw6|in Latin in favour of the burial of Galileo in Santa Croce, and the erection of a monument. Written to refute the objections of those who considered him a heretic. Document affirming the validity of Galileo's will, and his right to make a will: with holograph endorsement by Fra Giovanni Paolo Bimbacci. Produced in Florence. ### Publication/Creation  c. 1642  ### Physical description  ...    ### Notes The objectors were partly successful, and Galileo was buried in an obscure part of the Church. His remains were not removed until 17
